New Records: England scored their highest total of 339 in the match.
Ben Stokes scored 108 runs, contributing significantly to England's win.
The Netherlands were dismissed for 179, their lowest score in the series.
Key Match Events: Chris Woakes and Ben Stokes formed a record partnership to rescue England's innings.
Paul van Meekeren was dismissed by Moeen Ali in a key moment.
England's bowlers took crucial wickets, including Roelof van der Merwe and Logan van Beek.
Pre-Game Insights: England elected to bat first after winning the toss.
The Netherlands had recurring batting issues, as noted by their captain Scott Edwards.
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler expressed relief at the win and acknowledged the team's resilience.
Scott Edwards highlighted the need for improved batting consistency.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was attended by 9,217 fans in Pune.
The win marked England's end of a five-match losing streak.
Others: The match was part of the ICC Cricket World Cup 2023-24 series.
